HEADWORD: Cytoblast
<hw>Cy"to*blast</hw> <pr>(s?"t?-bl?st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ky`tos</grk> hollow vessel + <ets>-blast</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The nucleus of a cell; the germinal or active
spot of a cellule, through or in which cell development takes
place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cytoblastema</ent>⟦br⟧
